This paper is about simulating and predicting the evolution of a large collaborative software-development ecosystem using agent-based simulations. It involves massive amounts of data and requires machine learning and statistical methods to analyze the data and build the models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
